Eris is named after the greek goddess of strife and discord

Eris has an apparent magnitude of 18.7, making it bright enough to be detectable to some amateur telescopes. A 200-millimeter (7.9 in) telescope with a CCD can detect Eris under favorable conditions.

Eris is named after the Greek goddess of strife and discord.
It's a little more massive than Pluto, and it's also the largest body
orbiting the Sun that we haven't sent a spacecraft to.

